approach to providing constructive feedback in this situation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Ask the colleague for their self-assessment first","Focus on personality traits that need development","Delay feedback until the next scheduled performance review","Begin by highlighting all areas requiring improvement","Provide feedback in front of the entire team for learning purposes"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most effective approach is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eask the colleague for their self-assessment first\u003C/strong\u003E. This encourages self-reflection, demonstrates respect for their perspective, and helps create a collaborative dialogue about performance improvement.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect approaches are problematic because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBegin by highlighting all areas requiring improvement\u003C/strong\u003E - Starting with negative feedback can create defensiveness and reduce receptiveness to suggestions\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProvide feedback in front of the entire team for learning purposes\u003C/strong\u003E - Feedback should be given privately to maintain professional dignity and avoid embarrassment\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFocus on personality traits that need development\u003C/strong\u003E - Feedback should focus on specific, observable behaviors rather than personal characteristics\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDelay feedback until the next scheduled performance review\u003C/strong\u003E - Timely feedback is more effective as details are fresh and changes can be implemented immediately\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAfter obtaining their self-assessment, feedback should be specific, focused on behaviors that can be changed, and include actionable suggestions for improvement. This approach helps maintain a supportive learning environment while promoting professional development.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Constructive feedback should be specific, timely, and focused on observable behaviors rather than personality traits.","The feedback sandwich approach (positive-negative-positive) can reduce defensiveness but may dilute the impact of important feedback.","Effective feedback includes suggestions for improvement and creates an action plan for development."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65375"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18898"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65375","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65375"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-17T12:46:10+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-17T12:46:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11631"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80098"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7